<Author>unltdmind
<Content>Warning to travelers I just returned from Mexico and spent my last 3 nights at the Imperial. The business office use and internet was free - a great asset for me - the breakfast buffet included in our group's package was fabulous and most of the staff was very friendly and helpful.There were several members of our group who complained that their personal bags and suitcases had been ruffled through and some items were missing, including a cell phone. We checked out of the hotel one day early because of these incidences and also because the maint. department began a painting project that filled the entire atrium and thus the rooms with a very intense turpentine odor. We requested that they cease until after we departed. They agreed but continued to paint anyway. The next day we left the hotel when the odor was extremely bad and members of the group found personal items missing, but were unable to find another hotel that day for one night to accomodate the entire group. The Imperial promised to deal with the issues we presented. So we returned for the last night. The painting started again and it was the very last morning, during a meeting, when my own jewelry disappeared. I believe it to be a housekeeping management problem, and not the housekeepers necessarily. I hope to find resolution with them, but write this review prior to the end of this incident because the hotel administration appears to be accomodating but the behavior continues. 
